Patch Set 7: Workflow-1

Hemanth, Brian: please advise. After restricting 'data_api' option with 'choices' parameter, the functional test 'glance/tests/functional/v2/test_images.py' fails because it's trying to set the value to: 'glance.tests.functional.v2.registry_data_api', which is not one of the valid choices.

Patch Set 7:

I tried using set/clear_override on ConfigOpts object, but it didn't work. These options don't change the option definition but rather the option value passed in through config file, command line or default.

Let me ask a more existential question. Given that this set of tests is called TestImagesWithRegistry, why is it not using the real value of glance.db.registry.api? Why the need for this fake value? Is it because the Registry is a separate service and not running in the test env?

Patch Set 7:

> I tried using set/clear_override on ConfigOpts object, but it
 > didn't work. These options don't change the option definition but
 > rather the option value passed in through config file, command line
 > or default.
 > 
 > Let me ask a more existential question. Given that this set of
 > tests is called TestImagesWithRegistry, why is it not using the
 > real value of glance.db.registry.api? Why the need for this fake
 > value? Is it because the Registry is a separate service and not
 > running in the test env?

If we have to use a mock value in this test, then the best way to do this seems to be to mock the DB API module: 'glance.db.__init__.get_api'

can we change the functional test for this opt?
